silvia
------------------------------------------
Silvia is a C++ implementation of the IRMA card communication protocol. The
software can be used to issue credentials to an IRMA card and can verify
already issued credentials. Moreover, using this library, the cardholder can
delete their credentials from the card, read the log, print the contents of a
given credential stored in the IRMA card and update their PINs.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgmp10-6.3.0-1
  libnfc5-1.7.1-1
  libpcsclite1-2.3.3-1bl1
  libsilvia-devel-0.2.2+git20160712-1bl2
  libsilvia0-0.2.2+git20160712-1bl2
  libssl1.0-1.0.2u+za-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  libxml2-2.10.4-2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
